						<div class="postbody">When writing to the IRQ latch register ($C000), in addition to setting the IRQ counter reload value, does it also trigger a reload request?  That is, is it necessary to write to the IRQ reload register ($C001) after setting the reload value or will the value get loaded automatically as a consequence of setting the value?<br /><br />I managed to fix the scroll-in effect of the menu screen in Mega Man 3 by having a write to $C000 mean that a reload is requested as well.  But, it's unclear from the documentation if this is the way that MMC3 is supposed to function.<br /><br />Also, in Super Mario Bros 3, is PPU rendering disabled for one scanline directly above the status bar?  My emulator is producing a mostly hidden line.</div>

