				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">zeroone wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">When writing to the IRQ latch register ($C000), in addition to setting the IRQ counter reload value, does it also trigger a reload request?  That is, is it necessary to write to the IRQ reload register ($C001) after setting the reload value or will the value get loaded automatically as a consequence of setting the value?</div><br /><br />Writing $C000 changes the reload value only. It does not affect the value in the counter. It does not &quot;trigger a reload&quot;. The reload value is loaded into the counter when the counter value reaches 0. So to do this, you need to write the desired value to $C000 and then write to $C001 to zero the counter value. This means the next time a scanline is detected it will see the counter is zero and will reload with the reload value. This will not trigger an IRQ because an IRQ is only generated if the value is 1 and being decreased to 0.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

