				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Using the FCEUX debugger, I stepped over the IRQ code.  It writes 64 to $C000 (the IRQ Latch register) on scanline 88, but it never writes to $C001 (the IRQ Reload register).  If $C000 does not automatically trigger a reload, how does this code work?<br /><br />Edit: I think I finally got this working.<br /><br />I reviewed the MMC3 bullet points here: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://kevtris.org/mappers/mmc3/">http://kevtris.org/mappers/mmc3/</a><!-- m -->  Here are the key ones:<br /><br />1. Writing to C000h DOES NOT affect the IRQ counter.  When the IRQ counter expires and reloads, it will use the new value written.<br />2. Whenever the IRQ counter changes from a non-zero value to 00h, the IRQ flag will be set if it is enabled.<br />3. Writing to C001h will clear the IRQ counter, and it will be reloaded from C000h into the IRQ counter on the NEXT rising edge of A12. It will decrement from that point on subsequent A12 rising edges.<br />4. Once the IRQ counter reaches 00h, the NEXT rising edge of A12 will copy C000h's value into the counter.<br /><br />The Mega Man 3 menu screen relies on that fact that the IRQ handler runs when the counter transitions from 1 to 0, but the counter is only reset when A12 goes high on the subsequent scanline.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

